latestIgtvVideos.caption:
~I looked and looked at her, and I knew, as clearly as I know that I will die, that I loved her more than anything I had seen or imagined on earth...She could fade and wither - I didn't care. i would still go mad with tenderness at the mere sight of her face. If a violin string could ache, I would be that string~

Words taped together from Vladimir Nabokov's Lolita. 

Shot this in Feb/March '21
@jeffgoldbergstudio
@pynkmoss 

I've cut teeth with love scenes often but I also really want to do a few where couples obliterate each other - explore the range of 'love' this loosely defined rarely understood forever changing in meaning word.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Catch-22
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
We adapted and shot a scene out of Joseph Heller's Catch-22 for classwork...among the funnier books I've read off late, it served me well because I'm always looking for scenes and monologues outside of the mainstream. It was written as a comedy scene but we ended up giving it the sadboi treatment. I even have my sadboi voice on. 

One of my nicer attempts I reckon. When I work earnestly and honestly, things turn out alright. Thanks for letting us cut our teeth in front of a camera @jeffgoldbergstudio 

Edit: @pynkmoss
@saraporbanderwala

latestIgtvVideos.title: scene work at acting school, Dec 2019.
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Almost a year and a half ago, I shot these scene with my then classmate @sharvibhujbal7 

Adapted from a Pakistani movie titled 'Cake'. As a student I know I have my work cut out for me and I'm confident that I will become a better actor as I push the envelope. 1% better or more in comparison to the last time, that's my aim every time. 

With this one I remember Mitch from Dazed and Confused, in the film he'd always resort to fiddling with his hair as an acting crutch: this I'd like to work on and break. That said, I know I can do better, but I'm happy with attempting to make some bold choices like with the medicines and generally taunting my sister. In my journey that should hopefully culminate in me getting some work as an actor, I'm happy to be 'failing upwards' and not plateauing. Hoping to be more sincere and truthful with the opportunities to act I get henceforth. 

Thank you @jeffgoldbergstudio @pynkmoss

latestIgtvVideos.title: Eastwind Academy Philosophy of Music ep 7: Internet Music
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Got to be a part of a podcast a few weeks ago.  We discussed intention, how suddenly being sad on the internet is a new cool thing, how ironic expression like vaporwave and use of words like "aesthetic" actually became victims of the beast they were trying to mock and expose: Capitalism etc etc etc 
Vaporwave in its truest sense has always showed us the fault in our generation - excess consumerism as a means to cope with society's idea of what/how an individual should be - further worsened by the likes of this platform where images of other people's seemingly perfect lives does more harm than good always making us long for a life always out of reach either in the past or future. it's a long talk, on Eastwind's YouTube if you'd like to give it a listen. :) [here's a snippet]

childPosts.alt: Photo by Adi on May 26, 2025. May be a meme of text that says 'You're interested in picking up DJing and want to know about $. Your DJ rate is determined by a weird mix of your skill, time in the game, who you know, how well you know them, your popularity the venue and sound you'd play etc. There's no set way to set a price. You have a different rate for clubs, for friends and family, for brands, weddings, small gigs for the scene etc etc. But never play for free.'.

Photo by Adi on May 26, 2025. May be an image of cigarette and text that says 'It hurts you, 'the scene', and only benefits people that run the show but don't care for it. Know these perils of pro-bono performance Word travels, every DJ knows how much the other is making. If you play for free, that brand sticks, it takes years to undo that rep. They'll dangle the 'exposure' carrot in front of you and make you play a warm up set at 9pm to an empty room- there is no real exposure.'.

Photo by Adi on May 26, 2025. May be an image of magazine and text that says 'You'll be offered 'sick footage' and your name δη a flyer- that means nothing when you can arrange that yourself with some hustle. You'll get to 'practice on CDJs in a big club'- you can rent a studio for an hour and achieve the same and get better in the process. •Most importantly it starts a price war which is bad for the whole industry. You playing for free drives down the price for ~every other DJ operating at your level! (Economics lesson'.

Photo by Adi on April 19, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'Being in the mix is deeply meditative. You stand in one place, scan the room, pick a track, play it, find another track, listen to it in your headphones, mix it in, remove the first track, reset the mixer. Rinse. Repeat. This happens in 2 minutes. You do it for 4 hours. Eyes, ears, hands, feet: all present always.'.

You can't roll your eyes, but you note their lack of originality and taste. Many are far too comfortable telling a DJ/actor or any other artist/entertainer how to do their job but won't tell a pilot how to fly a plane. That baffles me most.'.

latestPosts.caption:
This one's for my 'bro help me with my DJing' crew.

I rant about charlatans in our DJ scene but it might just be easier to make them better than wishing for them to vanish. 

Love my local and random internet tastemakers :)

*words probably relevant if you're booked for a gig where you don't have to play pop/commercial music.

Lots of inner turmoil w the state of our scene haha. I'm figuring it out as I go along, making it up as I go along. Tryna be the friendly neighborhood vibes guy. 

*for that one ideal booking where the brief is simply to 'send it 🏄🏼‍♂️'

Feels like I play more rooftops, beaches, and outdoor venues than actual clubs. Sri Lanka was great, very lazy, very hot, very disco-ey. Southern SL's House scene is sickkkk 🤙🏽

Lately, for no reason whatsoever, I've been having visions of myself lounging and playing disco somewhere in North Africa. Egypt? Tunisia? Morocco? Algeria? 👀

#dj #disco #house #srilanka #mirissa #india #music

familiarity had started to breed contempt, but I have returned energised. I love DJing man. 

weekends till mid-march are now committed here, there, somewhere, see you :)

Us young, big city people, we keep up with life in here -> 🧠
But not in here -> 🫀

I'm putting together puzzle pieces and the image I've had for my life has stayed the same all these years - there are electric guitars, there is something to do in the water, there are coconuts, afternoon naps, and not too much pressure to be or become someone. 

What a wholesome and exhausting week. #surf #rookie #fun

I'm hoping some clarity comes to me randomly on a Thursday afternoon. 

My dear friend @notakash_j was kind and offered to click some pictures of me. They look very retro and I quite like them.

I have been documenting myself at least once a year since I have very few pictures of me (possibly just a couple) from age 7 to 14. :/
